               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1226" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1226" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1226" type="surname" value="HAWKINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1226" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HAWKINS</persName>
                  </hi>, <hi rend="italic">mariner, Salisbury-place, Rotherhithe.</hi> On Wednesday,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184406100176"></xptr>
               <p>the 29th of May, I was at Greenwich fair—I had a handkerchief, which I lost out of my pocket—this is it—I know it by a darn.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1227" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1227" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1227" type="surname" value="CARPENTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1227" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CARPENTER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 84.) I was at the fair, and saw the prisoners following the prosecutor through the fair—Hill went behind him, and tried to get his handkerchief—he left him for a minute or two, and then Evans pushed Hill in front of the prosecutor, Hill put his head on the prosecutor's breast, and Evans took out the handkerchief—they both went away—Evans was about giving Hill the handkerchief, when I caught hold of both their hands with it.</p>
               <p>
